<subSubSection id="073632C6E0D0AEB754652282928463AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph id="347E1DC3C7179193E140CF76464137AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="596ABACA881AE20AC7DC71B360D37071" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation id="E8F539059BC92936C907278019AF7A63" author="Clos, D" journalOrPublisher="Flora Chilena" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="462 - 472" refId="B6" refString="Clos, D, 1849. Eritrichium. Flora Chilena 4 (4): 462 - 472" title="Eritrichium." volume="4" year="1849">
<normalizedToken id="F8B649DF5FDCAA07748A2A1119EDFD66" originalValue="Clos’">Clos'</normalizedToken>
(1849)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="E4D312D7C57E05371CFB73D1D5BA2AE2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium globuliferum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="globuliferum">
<emphasis id="6ED67AB8D2974EBEBD373B61AC0E2F23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium globuliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on two syntypes from Chile. The first collection was made by C. Gay (no. 
<emphasis id="E8A66DE01AF8CC58E8CBD8E0539698C8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">47</emphasis>
) in Coquimbo, while the other one was also made by him (
<emphasis id="75589FE7854393392C745D198409E705" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">s.n.</emphasis>
) in 
<normalizedToken id="C6B1CBC70C15A4C44CA16A965A5143F0" originalValue="Copiapó">Copiapo</normalizedToken>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="59931A590957A75E487A0A14D3E12B85" author="Perez-Moreau, RL" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" refId="B30" refString="Perez-Moreau, RL, 1976. Revision del genero Cryptantha en la Argentina (Boraginaceae). Darwiniana 20(1/2): 155-188." title="Revision del genero Cryptantha en la Argentina (Boraginaceae). Darwiniana 20 (1 / 2): 155 - 188." year="1976">
<normalizedToken id="6CE6E77AA4EF92FF9BB6DDDF93DDCFD9" originalValue="Pérez-Moreau">Perez-Moreau</normalizedToken>
(1976)
</bibRefCitation>
discussed this name and its original material, stating &quot;Chile. Coquimbo, 
<normalizedToken id="3390D17E407F2A5E745EB0679CB42143" originalValue="común">comun</normalizedToken>
en dunas de la costa, La Serena, C. Gay 47, IX-1836 (tipo de 
<taxonomicName id="D0D8D6D75DBFA5EDC3EBAE63A7A40972" genus="E." lsidName="E. globuliferum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="globuliferum">
<emphasis id="537FF96B97E7BDF5FE89B28931FC8937" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">E. globuliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, P)&quot;. However, 
<normalizedToken id="70D093F0EC3483CD636DDC38DCBAC94B" originalValue="Pérez-Moreau’s">Perez-Moreau's</normalizedToken>
statement is insufficiently precise since it cannot be ascertained to which of the two specimens at P he was referring. Thus, his choice is here interpreted as a first-step lectotypification. In order to narrow this designation, the specimen P00606762 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="727DF3FA9D2F4F1F4BC59A8EF1DDCE85" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
In describing 
<taxonomicName id="AF8AEDBC85459C2FB99E589B619CFC02" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1864" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium glareosum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glareosum">
<emphasis id="2AB75921654925860D5DD0125A9AC095" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium glareosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FAAF901021508C3C0E0CA5558CA50C46" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Linnaea" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 308" refId="B36" refString="Philippi, RA, 1864. Plantarum novarum Chilensium. Linnaea 33: 1 - 308" title="Plantarum novarum Chilensium." volume="33" year="1864">Rudolph A. Philippi (1864)</bibRefCitation>
cited a collection made in &quot;alveo fluminis Aconcagua&quot;, Chile. Two specimens of this collection in agreement with the protologue are found at SGO. These duplicates all bear original labels annotated by Philippi with the identification of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="7FB21A2C7EE82126DD657A6E1BE8C41E" genus="E." lsidName="E. glareosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="glareosum">E. glareosum</taxonomicName>
&quot; and agree with the diagnosis cited in the protologue. 
<bibRefCitation id="C94BA29376C13A9B0A22A04886AF4E4A" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
referred to a sheet lodged at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken id="374DAC277ABA237696BEF8CF7C58E712" originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
of 
<taxonomicName id="56F091DFAF708846A959102332F4B127" genus="E." lsidName="E. glareosum" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" rank="species" species="glareosum">
<emphasis id="76848B222BDC4ED3AEDD74D3D87C7F39" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">E. glareosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, thus, his statement is here interpreted as a first-step lectotype designation. In order to narrow this earlier designation, the specimen SGO000004086 is here selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0294B0B407DE4B4C686068E2A5895C06" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<bibRefCitation id="EC51FCAE0727B237FC9377B9C358CD3E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="511 - 566" refId="B39" refString="Philippi, RA, 1895. Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion). Anales de la Universidad de Chile 90: 511 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" title="Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion)." url="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" volume="90" year="1895">Rudolph A. Philippi (1895)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4A495A6AE16C6B5BA34AB52B4AC95803" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium carrizalense" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carrizalense">
<emphasis id="93EDA3560A8C98C6E4387353552B9410" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium carrizalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a Rosario Godoy de Callao collection made in Yerba Buena, Chile. A duplicate of this material, annotated in 
<normalizedToken id="D7793F493CADB726C947B5AC2706E742" originalValue="Philippi’s">Philippi's</normalizedToken>
hand as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="A01B7184BE1A58B77C235BC4E50AE085" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium carrizalense" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carrizalense">Eritrichium carrizalense</taxonomicName>
&quot;, was lodged at B and now destroyed but a photograph from 
<normalizedToken id="B443490002DE40A502AA77098F937A08" originalValue="Macbride’s">Macbride's</normalizedToken>
Berlin negatives (neg. 17371) is available at F with a copy at GH. Furthermore, there is a duplicate at herbarium SGO and fragments of the syntype at B lodged at GH. 
<bibRefCitation id="3A730E95759F93C32A8CBBC3629E0C18" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
referred to the original material of this name, stating that the 
<normalizedToken id="87DF436D6E2F28519D63E55F483EE77E" originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
was lodged at SGO; in the protologue of the species, however, there is no indication of any particular specimen as such. Thus, 
<bibRefCitation id="0862E9B715EF4F897C1F40B10B2A71F0" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken id="2B3161778C8CC1FBAC31FE9757DFD343" originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
statement is here interpreted as a lectotype designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CDE05E413CA97436ED6F2D263BF0A7F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="DB7652E24B5DD4D387E619D96225741F" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium sphaerophorum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sphaerophorum">
<emphasis id="6F91F5C01A3E6FB60256E78538F87189" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Eritrichium sphaerophorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FC4667C422D72AB169B2A36091389E64" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" author="Philippi, RA" journalOrPublisher="Anales de la Universidad de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="511 - 566" refId="B39" refString="Philippi, RA, 1895. Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion). Anales de la Universidad de Chile 90: 511 - 566, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" title="Plantas nuevas chilenas de las familias que corresponden al tomo IV de la obra de Gay: (continuacion)." url="https://doi.org/10.5354/0717-8883.2012.20872" volume="90" year="1895">Philippi 1895</bibRefCitation>
) includes a direct reference to a collection made by Rudolph A. Philippi near Caldera, Chile, in 1879. 
<bibRefCitation id="202D26FBDAAECC9FF8C2B7C4E3BFC4A5" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
clearly indicated a sheet housed at SGO as the 
<normalizedToken id="9AE1B8C69262CF055DB1C3F64CB1A23A" originalValue="“type”">&quot;type&quot;</normalizedToken>
, although an additional element, also annotated in 
<normalizedToken id="12457690EFAC2053FBB5FA2AB656962C" originalValue="Philippi’s">Philippi's</normalizedToken>
hand as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="6015307F442E3F1B661E7E85F7824F5F" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1895" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Eritrichium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eritrichium sphaerophorum" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sphaerophorum">Eritrichium sphaerophorum</taxonomicName>
&quot; was located there in agreement with the protologue. In this context, 
<bibRefCitation id="B7D778A5A8EC612393A8B1DCE3FF26FF" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken id="E2E2C12F633ABAD8AECC00EDD141D812" originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
choice is here interpreted as a first-step lectotypification. In order to narrow this designation, the specimen SGO000004137 is selected as a second-step lectotype.
</paragraph>
